A 22-year-old guard, Zachariah Yahaya, yesterday appeared at a Tinubu Magistrates’ Court for allegedly breaking into his employer’s home and stealing electrical appliances. Yahaya pleaded not guilty. Prosecuting Assistant Superintendent of Police (ASP) Fidelis Dike alleged that the defendant committed the offence on January 31 at 1am at Plot 26, Bisola Durosimi-Etti Street, Lekki Phase 1, Lagos. He alleged that the defendant, a guard and others at large, burgled the home of his employer, Mr. Mohammed Odunowo, and stole electrical appliances worth N650,000. “The defendant burgled the apartment and the car of his employer, while he was away and stole two Plasma TV sets, two car television sets and one car centre console, all valued at N650,000,”  Dike said. Magistrate T. A. Anjorin-Ajose granted the defendant N200,000 bail with two sureties in the like sum. He said one of the sureties must be a relation of the defendant and the other a civil servant. The case continues on March 14.